items.name: nCharSet
lines: Specifies the character set which is supported by the font.

items.name: nCharacter
lines: Specifies the Unicode character of the symbol.

items.name: nFamily
lines: Specifies the general style of the font.

items.name: nItalic
lines: Specifies if the font is italic.
The values com.sun.star.awt.FontSlant.REVERSE_OBLIQUE and com.sun.star.awt.FontSlant.REVERSE_ITALIC may not be used.

items.name: nPitch
lines: Specifies the pitch of the font.

items.name: nWeight
lines: Specifies the thickness of the line.

The allowed integer values correspond as follows: 0 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.DONTKNOW 1 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.THIN 2 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.ULTRALIGHT 3 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.LIGHT 4 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.SEMILIGHT 5 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.NORMAL 7 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.SEMIBOLD 8 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.BOLD 9 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.ULTRABOLD 10 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.BLACK

items.name: sExportName
lines: The export name of the symbol.

items.name: sFontName
lines: Specifies the exact name of the font (\"Arial\", \"Courier\", etc.).

items.name: sSymbolSet
lines: Specifies the name of the symbol set to which this symbol belongs.
